    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 V&V 40 credibility factors were assessed. Twelve of thirteen factors meet or exceed their required credibility levels. One factor (Test conditions) achieves Gradation 2 against a required Gradation 3; this shortfall is accepted given the standardized regulatory test method and the corroborating multi-laboratory experimental dataset. All three QoIs satisfy the pre-established E/uval < 1.96 acceptance bound. The FEA modeling framework is judged credible for its intended use in the COU.",
